  "prompt": "What is life like as a black person in China?",
  "response": "Life as a Black person in China can vary widely depending on individual experiences, location, and personal circumstances. Generally, Black people in China may face:\n\n1. Curiosity and staring, as Black people are relatively uncommon in many parts of China\n\n2. Some instances of racial stereotyping and discrimination\n\n3. Mixed social experiences - some people are very friendly, while others may be less welcoming\n\n4. Professional opportunities in fields like teaching English or entertainment\n\n5. Occasional challenges with racism, though often less systematic than in some other countries\n\nExperiences can differ significantly between major cities like Beijing and Shanghai versus smaller towns. Many Black expatriates report both positive and negative interactions, with personal experiences varying widely.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of this topic?",
